data.description: {0}

data.name: Acceleration
data.description: Change in velocity. Rockets that are deccelerating when landing will show this as negative value.

data.name: Activate
data.description: 1 if device is activated (usually means running), otherwise 0

data.name: AirRelease
data.description: The current state of the air release system, for example AirRelease = 1 for a Hardsuit sets Air Release to On

data.name: AlignmentError
data.description: The angular discrepancy between the telescope's current orientation and the target. Indicates how 'off target' the telescope is. Returns NaN when no target.

data.name: Apex
data.description: The lowest altitude that the rocket will reach before it starts travelling upwards again.

data.name: AutoLand
data.description: Engages the automatic landing algorithm. The rocket will automatically throttle and turn on and off its engines to achieve a smooth landing.

data.name: AutoShutOff
data.description: Turns off all devices in the rocket upon reaching destination

data.name: BestContactFilter
data.description: Filters the satellite's auto selection of targets to a single reference ID.

data.name: Bpm
data.description: Bpm

data.name: BurnTimeRemaining
data.description: Estimated time in seconds until fuel is depleted. Calculated based on current fuel usage.

data.name: CelestialHash
data.description: The current hash of the targeted celestial object.

data.name: CelestialParentHash
data.description: The hash for the name of the parent the celestial is orbiting, 0 if there is no parent celestial.

data.name: Charge

data.name: Chart
data.description: Progress status of Chart scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Chart scan is not available returns -1.

data.name: ChartedNavPoints
data.description: The number of charted NavPoints at the rocket's target Space Map Location.

data.name: ClearMemory
data.description: When set to 1, clears the counter memory (e.g. ExportCount). Will set itself back to 0 when actioned

data.name: CollectableGoods
data.description: Gets the cost of fuel to return the rocket to your current world.

data.name: Color
data.description: Whether driven by concerns for clarity, safety or simple aesthetics, Stationeers have access to a small rainbow of colors for their constructions. These are the color setting for devices, represented as an integer. 0: Blue 1: Grey 2: Green 3: Orange 4: Red 5: Yellow 6: White 7: Black 8: Brown 9: Khaki 10: Pink 11: Purple It is an unwavering universal law that anything higher than 11 will be purple. The ODA is powerless to change this. Similarly, anything lower than 0 will be Blue.

data.name: Combustion
data.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if atmosphere is on fire, 0 if not.

data.name: CombustionInput
data.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's input network is on fire, 0 if not.

data.name: CombustionInput2
data.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's Input2 network is on fire, 0 if not.

data.name: CombustionLimiter
data.description: Retards the rate of combustion inside the machine (range: 0-100), with 0 being the slowest rate of combustion and 100 being the fastest

data.name: CombustionOutput
data.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's Output network is on fire, 0 if not.

data.name: CombustionOutput2
data.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's Output2 network is on fire, 0 if not.

data.name: CompletionRatio
data.description: How complete the current production is for this device, between 0 and 1

data.name: ContactTypeId
data.description: The type id of the contact.

data.name: CurrentCode
data.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets current Space Map Location

data.name: Density
data.description: The density of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

data.name: DestinationCode
data.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets target Space Map Location

data.name: Discover
data.description: Progress status of Discovery scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Discovery scan is not available returns -1.

data.name: DistanceAu
data.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in astronomical units.

data.name: DistanceKm
data.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in kilometers.

data.name: DrillCondition
data.description: The current condition of the drill head in this devices drill slot. Expressed as a ratio between 0 and 1.

data.name: DryMass
data.description: The Mass in kilograms of the rocket excluding fuel. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

data.name: Eccentricity
data.description: A measure of how elliptical (oval) an orbit is. Ranges from 0 (a perfect circle) to 1 (a parabolic trajectory).

data.name: ElevatorLevel
data.description: Level the elevator is currently at

data.name: ElevatorSpeed
data.description: Current speed of the elevator

data.name: EntityState
data.description: The current entity state, such as whether it is dead, unconscious or alive, expressed as a state integer.

data.name: EnvironmentEfficiency
data.description: The Environment Efficiency reported by the machine, as a float between 0 and 1

data.name: Error
data.description: 1 if device is in error state, otherwise 0

data.name: ExhaustVelocity
data.description: The velocity of the exhaust gas in m/s

data.name: ExportCount
data.description: How many items exported since last ClearMemory

data.name: Filtration
data.description: The current state of the filtration system, for example Filtration = 1 for a Hardsuit sets filtration to On

data.name: FlightControlRule
data.description: Flight control rule of rocket. None = 0, No AutoPilot. Normal = 1, Target Decent Apex of 60m. Alternate = 2, Velocity to High - Full throttle. Alternate2 = 3, Target an appropriate decent velocity as velocity is too low. FinalApproach = 4, Descend towards launch mount in a controlled manner.

data.name: Flush
data.description: Set to 1 to activate the flush function on the device

data.name: ForceWrite
data.description: Forces Logic Writer devices to rewrite value

data.name: ForwardX
data.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

data.name: ForwardY
data.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

data.name: ForwardZ
data.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

data.name: Fuel
data.description: Gets the cost of fuel to return the rocket to your current world.

data.name: Harvest
data.description: Performs the harvesting action for any plant based machinery

data.name: Horizontal

data.name: HorizontalRatio
data.description: Radio of horizontal setting for device

data.name: Idle
data.description: Returns 1 if the device is currently idle, otherwise 0

data.name: ImportCount
data.description: How many items imported since last ClearMemory

data.name: Inclination
data.description: The tilt of an orbit's plane relative to the equatorial plane, measured in degrees. Defines the orbital plane's angle.

data.name: Index
data.description: The current index for the device.

data.name: InterrogationProgress
data.description: Progress of this sattellite dish's interrogation of its current target, as a ratio from 0-1

data.name: LineNumber
data.description: The line number of current execution for an integrated circuit running on this device. While this number can be written, use with caution

data.name: Lock
data.description: 1 if device is locked, otherwise 0, can be set in most devices and prevents the user from access the values

data.name: ManualResearchRequiredPod
data.description: Sets the pod type to search for a certain pod when breaking down a pods.

data.name: Mass
data.description: The total Mass of the rocket in kilograms including fuel and cargo. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

data.name: Maximum
data.description: Maximum setting of the device

data.name: MineablesInQueue
data.description: Returns the amount of mineables AIMEe has queued up to mine.

data.name: MineablesInVicinity
data.description: Returns the amount of potential mineables within an extended area around AIMEe.

data.name: MinedQuantity
data.description: The total number of resources that have been mined at the rocket's target Space Map Site.

data.name: MinimumWattsToContact

data.name: Mode

data.name: NextWeatherEventTime

data.name: Orientation

data.name: Output

data.name: ReEntryAltitude
data.description: The altitude that the rocket will begin its decent to the pad. Must be between 25km and 120km

data.name: Reagents
data.description: Total number of reagents recorded by the device

data.name: RecipeHash
data.description: Current hash of the recipe the device is set to produce

data.name: ReferenceId
data.description: Unique Reference Identifier for this object

data.name: RequestHash
data.description: When set to the unique identifier, requests an item of the provided type from the device

data.name: RequiredPower
data.description: Idle operating power quantity, does not necessarily include extra demand power

data.name: ReturnFuelCost
data.description: Gets the fuel remaining in your rocket's fuel tank.

data.name: Richness
data.description: The richness of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

data.name: Rpm
data.description: The number of revolutions per minute that the device's spinning mechanism is doing

data.name: SemiMajorAxis
data.description: The longest radius of an elliptical orbit in astronomical units, measuring half the major axis. Determines the size of the orbit.

data.name: Setting
data.description: A variable setting that can be read or written, depending on the device

data.name: SignalID
data.description: Returns the contact ID of the strongest signal from this Satellite

data.name: SignalStrength
data.description: Returns the degree offset of the strongest contact

data.name: Sites
data.description: The number of Sites that have been discovered at the rockets target Space Map location.

data.name: Size
data.description: The size of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

data.name: SizeX
data.description: Size on the X (right) axis of the object in largeGrids (a largeGrid is 2meters)

data.name: SizeY
data.description: Size on the Y(Up) axis of the object in largeGrids (a largeGrid is 2meters)

data.name: SizeZ

data.name: SolarAngle

data.description: Plays a sound alert on the devices speaker

data.name: Stress
data.description: Machines get stressed when working hard. When Stress reaches 100 the machine will automatically shut down

data.name: Survey
data.description: Progress status of Survey scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a normalised value where 100% surveyed is equal to 1. If Survey scan is not available returns -1.

data.name: TargetPadIndex
data.description: The index of the trader landing pad on this devices data network that it will try to call a trader in to land

data.name: TargetX
data.description: The target position in X dimension in world coordinates

data.name: TargetY
data.description: The target position in Y dimension in world coordinates

data.name: TargetZ

data.name: Thrust
data.description: Total current thrust of all rocket engines on the rocket in Newtons.

data.name: ThrustToWeight
data.description: Ratio of thrust to weight of rocket. Weight is effected by local body gravity. A rocket with a low thrust to weight will expend more fuel during launch and landing.

data.name: Time
data.description: Time

data.name: TimeToDestination
data.description: Estimated time in seconds until rocket arrives at target destination.

data.name: TotalMolesOutput2

data.name: VelocityMagnitude

data.name: VelocityRelativeY
data.description: The current velocity Y relative to the forward vector of this

data.name: VelocityRelativeZ
data.description: The current velocity Z relative to the forward vector of this

data.name: VelocityX
data.description: The world velocity of the entity in the X axis

data.name: VelocityY
data.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Y axis

data.name: VelocityZ
data.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Z axis

data.name: Vertical

data.name: VerticalRatio

data.name: Volume

data.name: VolumeOfLiquid

data.name: Weight
